                "code": "patient-history"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} was diagnosed with subclinical hypothyroidism at age 17 during a routine school health check; thyroid peroxidase antibodies were mildly elevated and she was commenced on low-dose levothyroxine, which she continues [MEDDIALOG:F32.9:0]. She has no prior psychiatric hospitalisations, though her general practitioner noted low mood during an appointment approximately one year ago and recommended lifestyle measures without formal treatment. There is no previous history of manic or hypomanic episodes. She has no other known chronic medical conditions beyond hypothyroidism. She uses an oral contraceptive (levonorgestrel) for cycle regulation. She uses gabapentin 100 mg at night, prescribed by a neurologist for tension-type headaches that began in the context of examination stress [MEDDIALOG:F32.9:5]. {patientName} denies current or past use of alcohol, cannabis, or any illicit substances [MEDDIALOG:F32.9:0]. She has a mild allergy to amoxicillin (urticaria). Family history is notable for recurrent depressive disorder in her mother and alcohol use disorder in her father. She attended one course of supportive psychological counselling via her university health service in 2023, which provided partial and temporary benefit."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
